  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `geth version`\r\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nno goroutine leak\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nline3 will be called in the main goroutine depends on the test logic. However, if nowaiting is called, it means that no waiting receiver. So sending operation at line 4, which will be called in `readLoop` will be blocked.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n```\r\nexpNotWaiting := func() {\r\n       if iter.waiting(time.Millisecond * 100) { // line 3\r\n           t.Fatalf(\"FillSet unexpectedly waiting for new nodes\")\r\n       }\r\n   }\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nfunc (i *testIter) Next() bool {\r\n   i.waitCh <- struct{}{} // line 4\r\n   i.node = <-i.nodeCh\r\n   return i.node != nil\r\n}\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\ngoroutine 8 [chan send]:\r\ngithub.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/les/vflux/client.(*testIter).Next(0xc00000c888, 0xc0000d60e0)\r\n   /repos/go-ethereum/les/vflux/client/fillset_test.go:40 +0xb1\r\ngithub.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/les/vflux/client.(*FillSet).readLoop(0xc0001466e0)\r\n   /repos/go-ethereum/les/vflux/client/fillset.go:87 +0x1bc\r\ncreated by github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/les/vflux/client.NewFillSet\r\n   /repos/go-ethereum/les/vflux/client/fillset.go:68 +0x16a\r\n````\r\n\r\nDo we have any way to clean up this goroutine when exit?\r\nWhen submitting logs: please submit them as text and not screenshots.",
